o8bw1jx8g.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0"><div class="component-social-share default" data-reactid=".xo8bw1jx8g.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0.0"><div class="share-item facebook" data-href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fsneaker-collection-annoys-girlfriend-advice&amp;t=What%20If%20Your%20Sneaker%20Collection%20Annoys%20Your%20Girlfriend%3F" data-reactid=".xo8bw1jx8g.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-facebook"><a href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fsneaker-collection-annoys-girlfriend-advice&amp;t=What%20If%20Your%20Sneaker%20Collection%20Annoys%20Your%20Girlfriend%3F" target="_blank" aria-label="Facebook" data-reactid=".xo8bw1jx8g.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-facebook.0"><span class="icon" data-reactid=".xo8bw1jx8g.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-facebook.0.0"></span><span class="label" data-reactid=".xo8bw1jx8g.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-facebook.0.1">Facebook</span></a></div><div class="share-item twitter" data-href="https://twitter.com/share?text=What%20If%20Your%20Sneaker%20Collection%20Annoys%20Your%20Girlfriend%3F&amp;via=GQMagazine&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fsneaker-collection-annoys-girlfriend-advice" data-reactid=".xo8bw1jx8g.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-twitter"><a href="https://twitter.com/share?text=What%20If%20Your%20Sneaker%20Collection%20Annoys%20Your%20Girlfriend%3F&amp;via=GQMagazine&amp;url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fsneaker-collection-annoys-girlfriend-advice" target="_blank" aria-label="Twitter" data-reactid=".xo8bw1jx8g.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-twitter.0"><span class="icon" data-reactid=".xo8bw1jx8g.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-twitter.0.0"></span><span class="label" data-reactid=".xo8bw1jx8g.1.1.0.0.1.3.0.0.1.0.0.0:$share-item-twitter.0.1">Twitter</span></a></div></div></div></div></div></div></div></div><div class="body-text" data-reactid=".xo8bw1jx8g.1.1.0.0.4"><p data-reactid=".xo8bw1jx8g.1.1.0.0.4.0"><strong>My boyfriend is a sneakerhead, and I find it extremely annoying. I keep telling him that it&#x2019;s childish and expensive. He says I don&#x2019;t understand because I&#x2019;m a woman and only wear sneakers to the gym. When should a man give up chasing the latest sneakers?</strong><br>Let&#x2019;s establish a few things: </p><div class="embed ul" data-reactid=".xo8bw1jx8g.1.1.0.0.4.1"><ul><li>Loving sneakers isn&apos;t childish&#x2026;</li><li>&#x2026;though it definitely is expensive. </li><li>You don&#x2019;t understand being a sneakerhead because you&#x2019;re not into sneakers&#x2014;not because you&#x2019;re a woman. We don&#x2019;t let swerves perpetuate misogyny in this column. NOT IN MY HOUSE. [<a href="https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=zeqyC8m3nP0">Mutombo finger wag</a>]</li></ul></div><p data-reactid=".xo8bw1jx8g.1.1.0.0.4.2">Listen, I can see why you look at sneakerheads, your boyfriend included, as obsessive. I mean, Flight Club just launched a layaway program. The sneaker game has boiled over in some very extreme ways. But everybody loves something. Foodies. Watch collectors. Car nerds. Yeah, that passion can trip over into greed, but unless your boyfriend is spending your rent money on Jordans, I don&#x2019;t see the problem. If it&#x2019;s his money, and you&#x2019;re not being buried by box-fresh Yeezy Boosts every time you open a closet door, why take away something he enjoys? Think of it from his side: You only have one, maybe two, pairs of sneakers, right? And yet he accepts you and isn&#x2019;t writing advice columnists about your piss-poor sneaker game. So maybe just rise up and love through this.  </p><div class="embed callout" data-reactid=".xo8bw1jx8g.1.1.0.0.4.3"><div class="callout small" data-type="callout"><figure class="embedded-image" data-type="image"><div class="image-content"><div class="component-rendition"><div class="component-image loaded"><span><img src="http://media.gq.com/photos/55f191fae4fe554f30885d72/master/w_600/leon-bridges-gq-2015-02.jpg" alt="leon-bridges-gq-2015-02.jpg"></span></div></div><div class="component-social-share default"><div class="share-item facebook" data-href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fsneaker-collection-annoys-girlfriend-advice&amp;t=leon-bridges-gq-2015-02.jpg"><a href="https://www.facebook.com/sharer/sharer.php?u=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fsneaker-collection-annoys-girlfriend-advice&amp;t=leon-bridges-gq-2015-02.jpg" target="_blank" aria-label="Facebook"><span class="icon"></span><span class="label">Facebook</span></a></div><div class="share-item pinterest" data-href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fsneaker-collection-annoys-girlfriend-advice&amp;media=http%3A%2F%2Fmedia.gq.com%2Fphotos%2F55f191fae4fe554f30885d72%2F1%3A1%2Fw_680%2Cc_limit%2Fleon-bridges-gq-2015-02.jpg&amp;description=leon-bridges-gq-2015-02.jpg"><a href="https://www.pinterest.com/pin/create/button/?url=http%3A%2F%2Fwww.gq.com%2Fstory%2Fsneaker-collection-annoys-girlfriend-advice&amp;media=http%3A%2F%2Fmedia.gq.com%2Fphotos%2F55f191fae4fe554f30885d72%2F1%3A1%2Fw_680%2Cc_limit%2Fleon-bridges-gq-2015-02.jpg&amp;description=leon-bridges-gq-2015-02.jpg" target="_blank" aria-label="Pinterest"><span class="icon"></span><span class="label">Pinterest</span></a></div></div></div></figure></div></div><p data-reactid=".xo8bw1jx8g.1.1.0.0.4.5"><strong>Lately I&#x2019;ve been digging <a href="leon-bridges-soul-music">Leon Bridges&apos; throwback &#x2019;60s style</a>. I&apos;m a big guy, though&#x2014;250 pounds, but in shape&#x2014;so finding high-waisted pants is impossible. Help?</strong><br>Ever since the movie <em>Her</em> was released and showed us our phone-fornicating future, I&#x2019;ve felt like every guy should have at least one pair of high-waisted pants&#x2014;including you, big fella. They&apos;re a way to stand out in even the most basic outfit. The key to killing high-waisted pants is that they have to be slim, all the way down to the hem. (Leon Bridges, the smooth criminal, is stick-thin and can get away with his signature extra-wide pants. I&apos;d advise staying away from those.) To find your own pair, stop by a Brooks Brothers or your town&#x2019;s best old-school, no-nonsense haberdashery&#x2014;you know, where the salesmen have as many liver spots as they do ties&#x2014;and ask for pants in their most conservative fit. Chances are those pants will have a long rise&#x2014;but some wider legs. Swing by the tailor and put him to tapering. If you&#x2019;re really committed, you can scout for a vintage pair. This is the rare moment when eBay won&#x2019;t work for you&#x2014;you&apos;ll have to try on a bunch of pairs so you know for certain that you&#x2019;ll make Leon and Joaquin proud.  </p><p data-reactid=".xo8bw1jx8g.1.1.0.0.4.6"><strong>I&#x2019;ve been invited to a wedding where the ceremony&apos;s dress code is listed as &quot;upscale casual.&quot; After the reception everyone&#x2019;s heading to a drag show at a bar. (Go Supreme Court&#x2014;a legal gay wedding!) I want to follow the dress code without looking too nerdy, since I&#x2019;m single. What do I wear?</strong><br>First, let&#x2019;s toast one time to love winning, ya dig? Okay. &#x201C;Upscale casual&#x201D; isn&#x2019;t a real thing. That&#x2019;s the &#x201C;jumbo shrimp&#x201D; of dress codes. But it&#x2019;s your friends&#x2019; day, so we&#x2019;ll figure it out. I vote that you wear cocktail attire to both the ceremony and the after-party&#x2014;but still go for a costume change. Bring two suits, one light for everything up through the reception, one dark for the actual wedding. I&#x2019;m 27, which means I basically went on a world tour of weddings this summer. I wore the same suit to every single one (that wasn&#x2019;t black tie): a medium-gray hopsack two-piece from Boglioli. I went with black brogues and a white shirt and air tie or just a white T-shirt, depending on how dressy the vibe was. But if you want to go bolder, you could pair your suit with a fine-knit turtleneck, clean designer sneakers, or an exploded-print button-up&#x2014;not all at once, obviously&#x2014;and still nail whatever fabricated, &quot;upscale casual Armageddon-chic&quot; dress code you come across. </p><div class="embed hr" data-reactid=".xo8bw1jx8g.1.1.0.0.4.7"><hr></div><p data-reactid=".xo8bw1jx8g.1.1.0.0.4.8"><strong>The GQ Style Guy Is In!</strong> Send questions to <a href="mailto:Styleguy@GQ.com">Styleguy@GQ.com</a> or tweet <a href="https://twitter.com/gqstyleguy">@GQStyleGuy</a></p><p data-reactid=".xo8bw1jx8g.1.1.0.0.4.9"><strong>For more style tips, order our new <a href="https://w1.buysub.com/servlet/OrdersGateway?cds_mag_code=GQM&amp;cds_page_id=190810&amp;mbid=GQM_2015_SIP_FWStandalone_ONL_EDIT">GQ Style Guide</a>.</strong></p></div><div class="grid" data-reactid=".xo8bw1jx8g.1.1.0.0.5"><div class="row" data-reactid=".xo8bw1jx8g.1.1.0.0.5.0"><div class="col col-sm-15" data-reactid=".xo8bw1jx8g.1.1.0.0.5.0.0"><div class="component-topics" data-reactid=".xo8bw1jx8g.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0"><ul data-reactid=".xo8bw1jx8g.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0"><li data-reactid=".xo8bw1jx8g.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-0"><a href="http://www.gq.com/search?tags=Pants" data-reactid=".xo8bw1jx8g.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-0.0">Pants</a></li><li data-reactid=".xo8bw1jx8g.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-1"><a href="../search?tags=Sneakers" data-reactid=".xo8bw1jx8g.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-1.0">Sneakers</a></li><li data-reactid=".xo8bw1jx8g.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-2"><a href="../search?tags=Style%2520Guy" data-reactid=".xo8bw1jx8g.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-2.0">Style Guy</a></li><li data-reactid=".xo8bw1jx8g.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-3"><a href="../search?tags=Suits" data-reactid=".xo8bw1jx8g.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-3.0">Suits</a></li><li data-reactid=".xo8bw1jx8g.1.1.0.0.5.0.0.0.0.$topic-item-4"><a href="../search?tags=Weddings" data-re